it is possible to achieve it.', 2878, 0), (195136, 'If you wish for it, you can have it.', 2878, 0), (195137, 'You ought to be curious and daring.', 2878, 0), (195138, 'You can attain your highest potential.', 2878, 0), (195139, 'Trust the vibes you get, energy doesn’t lie.', 5287, 0), (195140, 'Why get bitter towards those who don''t believe in your dreams, when they don''t even believe in theirs?', 166, 0), (195141, 'When you begin to act on your dream it becomes a vision. When you stop acting on your vision it becomes a dream.', 11318, 0), (195142, 'The unpredictability of the future means absolutely nothing to the dreams of an ambitious positive mind.', 166, 0), (195143, 'A single lie is the father of all lies', 26761, 0), (195144, 'It''s hard to pay attention to those who don''t believe in you, when you are busy attending to the daily demands of your goals.', 166, 0), (195145, '...you are different from me, because you want to realize your dreams, I just want to dream...I''m afraid it will all be a disappointment, so I prefer just to dream...', 34, 0), (195146, 'One of the surest ways to give up on your goals, is to chase them all at once.', 166, 0), (195147, 'Forest is a dream where you may find yourself and dream is a forest where you may lose yourself!', 3701, 0), (195148, 'If your dreams don''t scare you, they are not big enough.', 14534, 0), (195149, 'I really miss the thought of you. I miss the hope that my future could''ve been a brilliant one–that you might have made it so. But I don''t regret the dream even if it''s gone now. And I want to thank you for inspiring it.', 35767, 0), (195150, 'Ella!” the voice yells, but I cannot tell where it is coming from. The sound wraps around me, spreading like spilt water and then evaporating into silence.“Where am I?” I whisper again.The darkness stretches out for eternity.I take a few steps forward, but the feeling is surreal—I cannot tell if I’ve actually moved or not, because everything is nothing. I feel something wet and warm slide down my cheek, and I touch the tear with my fingertips, swiping it away.Representative Belles is dead. I’m certain of that now. He’s gone. I’m… I’m in the place where he was, and now he’s gone, and now I’m stuck. I’m stuck in the nothingness of a dead body, and I don’t know how to get out.My heart thuds against my chest, and I gasp for air. What if I can never get out? What if eternity is nothing more than me, alone, in the darkness? Trapped in someone else’s death.I collapse, but it’s not like I fall on the floor. There is no floor. There was the illusion of one, but as my body gives way, I realize that I’m floating. I stretch out, my fingers and toes aching to feel, but there’s nothing, nothing at all, and I draw myself into myself, hugging my legs, my knees tucked under my chin.I’m alone.Maybe when Representative Belles died, I died too.Maybe this is it.', 763, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (195151, 'Interpreting dreams for Iranians was just as much a sacrament as reading coffee cups was for Turks', 23844, 0), (195152, 'When you dream, you activate the possibility of what some call impossible.', 5028, 0), (195153, 'Dreams often come true to those who clearly understand that there is a hefty price for every big prize.', 166, 0), (195154, 'Dreams only come true when you appoint strategic consistent actions to wake you up.', 166, 0), (195155, 'Inspiration for my short stories grows from a psychic kernel, a vision of some sort or an eccentric, colorful dream.', 3808, 0), (195156, 'Frustration fills his golden eyes. "What Queen? Who is coming?""The living myth," I whisper. "Dreams made flesh."His shock is replaced instantly by a fierce hunger. "You''re sure?"The room is a swirling mist. He''s the only thing still in sharp focus. He''s the only thing I need. "I saw her in the tangled web, Daemon. I saw her.', 968, 0), (195157, 'Your dreams can still be fully vindicated. The seeds of success and happiness are in all of us, but you must sow yours with faith.', 166, 0), (195158, 'Dream is meant to be original. There is no honor in trying to be a copy of someone else''s dream life.', 166, 0), (195159, 'You can deceive yourself with truth too. That''s an even more dangerous dream.', 2811, 0), (195160, 'Every dream has its success point, and you owe it to yourself to press forward until you reach yours.', 166, 0), (195161, 'Mercy and favor are miracles of God that give a man something he could not even dare to dream of.', 3800, 0), (195162, 'Stars are much further away from where they are now for those who have no dreams and no intentions to reach them!', 3701, 0), (195163, 'It is for this reason that we find that co-existence, which could neither be intime alone, for time has no contiguity, nor in space alone, forspace has no before, after, or now,', 1304, 0), (195164, 'Take a daily action to make your dreams a reality.', 2878, 0), (195165, 'It is almost impossible to be consistent with your goal, if your subconscious mind is constantly fed with negative perceptions of its road.', 166, 0), (195166, 'More than the sound of my own beating heart, I miss the sound of a ticking clock. Time passes, it must pass, but I have no more assurance of moving through time than I have that I am moving through space. In a way, I’m glad: this means perhaps 300 years and 364 days have passed, and tomorrow I will wake up. Sometimes after a cross-country meet or a long day at school, I’d fall into bed with all my clothes on and be out before I knew it. When I’d finally open my eyes, it would feel like I’d just shut them for a minute, but really, the whole rest of the day and half the night was gone. But. There were other times when I’d collapse onto my mattress, shut my eyes and dream, and it felt like I’d lived a whole lifetime in that dream, but when I woke up, it had only been a few minutes. What if only a year has gone by? What if we haven’t even left yet? That is my greatest fear.', 763, 0), (195167, 'Life. It’s about adventure, of having a dream and following it.', 5117, 0), (195168, 'Eventually, after much dreaming, the dream no longer suffices. You have to physically be there.', 5117, 0), (195169, 'Do not pursue what you cannot keep.', 3800, 0), (195170, 'Lying in my bed, I pray for a dreamless sleep... but if I am to dream, I want to dream of her.', 177, 0), (195171, 'Life is a very beautiful dream, he thought. I''m so glad I chose not to wake up from it just yet.', 28613, 0), (195172, 'Being different will always threaten the institution of understanding of a closed mind. However, evolution is built on difference, changing and the concept of thinking outside the box. Live to be your own unique brand, without apology.', 290, 0), (195173, 'Legend says that when you can''t sleep at night it''s because you''re awake in someone else''s dream', 35768, 0), (195174, 'A dream written down with a date becomes a goal. A goal broken down into steps becomes a plan. A plan backed by action makes your dreams come true.', 35769, 0), (195175, 'I had a dream I named my boat after you. I love to raise your mast.', 6509, 0), (195176, 'Recalling his first dreams of flight when he was a small child, Max acknowledged that his entire existence had been building up to this tipping point where he could finally choose to release his self-imposedlimitations.', 25241, 0), (195177, 'Is safety the ‘dream’ that will kill all of my other ‘dreams?’ For the truth is, no ‘real’ dream is safe.', 4397, 0), (195178, 'The cherished dream of every chessplayer is to play a match with the World Champion. But here is the paradox: the closer you come to the realization of this goal, the less you think about it.', 35770, 0), (195179, 'Majority of people don''t see the amount of work and years ambitious people invest behind the scenes, but as soon as they succeed with their dreams, they would insinuate that they were lucky.', 166, 0), (195180, 'Your true potential in life will always be greater than your biggest goals and dreams.', 166, 0), (195181, 'Quitting on one''s dreams isn''t a way out, because all it does is to bring forth some sufferings and quilts in one''s life.', 166, 0), (195182, 'The purpose of dreaming isn''t to dream forever, but to wake up from it.', 166, 0), (195183, 'Only those who dream with a sense of urgency get to wake up from their dreams.', 166, 0), (195184, 'If you are spending more time dreaming in your sleep than you do while awake, then you aren''t busy enough with your heart''s desires.', 166, 0), (195185, 'The purpose of every dream is to spend more time living in its reality than dreaming it.', 166, 0), (195186, 'Dare to dream and yearn to learn to cross the boundary of fears and doubts.', 2586, 0), (195187, 'At night I dream of things I scoff at by day.', 35771, 0), (195188, 'A person either buys his dream by surrendering his excuses or he buys his excuses by surrendering his dream.', 7677, 0), (195189, 'Dream, believe, strive, achieve.', 2586, 0), (195190, 'Let my memories of you be like water on the moon. A beautiful impossibility - but allowing me to sleep and dream of infinite beginnings rather than Othello endings.', 23450, 0), (195191, 'For as long as I write, I will never be lost.', 3305, 0), (195192, 'I do not understand why I was held back from Sedona for so many years. My spirit was broken down, and I lost everything, friends, pets, pieces of myself were lying everywhere. I felt like a massive failure from Boston, then a failure because I could not manifest Sedona. It almost seems like I had to give up, and let go of the iron grip I had on Sedona, in order to finally understand it better. Focusing on other dreams and paths, let me lighten up further, until it came unexpectedly at the door and knocked. "Remember Me? I am the dream you buried, and thought you would never get, but it feels right now, and you should just go for it".', 35772, 0), (195193, 'I think people give up, because it''s the easy option, but my goodness; why would giving up be easy? Your living your life chasing anything to fill the void of what came about when you let go of everything that mattered? I''d rather fight like mad, for everything that will ever matter, because giving in to anything that doesn''t will never cure the dream.', 3305, 0), (195194, 'Yes I believe a man will compliment my life oneday, but what''s the rush.. I mean everyone''s searching so passionately for something to fill the void and I don''t want any part in that, I''m happy finding my own way untill I get swept of my feet.', 3305, 0), (195195, 'Nothing came out. Suddenly I was hovering, looking down on myself from above.', 342, 0), (195196, 'Pain is something that we all feel sometimes; however, some of us see it as an opportunity for mental growth, while others interpret theirs as a definite end to their goals, dreams or desires.', 166, 0), (195197, 'Effective action is the air of every dream.', 166, 0), (195198, 'I find it a privilege and an honor to be human, for to me, one of the most wondrous and beautiful things in the universe, is found in human form. Because to be human, is to be able to dream dreams of pyramids and skyscrapers, and majestic works of art that spring from the human mind.', 20937, 0), (195199, 'Dream as big as you desire, but don''t forget to wake yourself from it with some consistent effective actions.', 166, 0), (195200, 'Don''t just dream because everyone around you is dreaming; instead, dream big because you deserve a better life, and can achieve it.', 166, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (195201, 'Still enveloped in a blanket of dreams he (life) continued to lie still, pretended as if he was in a deep slumber.', 8093, 0), (195202, 'The main wall that''s standing between you and success is having the courage to face your fear of failure. The foundation of success or failure can only be built with one''s thoughts and beliefs. Positive thoughts and beliefs breed positive results. However, positive thoughts without consistent actions make every dream a wishful thinking. Therefore, if you truly want success, you have to consistently think and work positively regardless of the circumstances you are faced with.', 166, 0), (195203, 'Three simple rules in life: If you do not go after what you want, you''ll never have it. If you do not ask, the answer will always be no. If you do not step forward, you will always be in the same place.', 33, 0), (195204, 'My heart broke a little at her unblemished view of life: She still believed in innocent secrets, the heady rush of a good mystery, and happily ever after... (I wasn''t about to disabuse her of those sweet notions.)...Little girls should be allowed to dream.', 2097, 0), (195205, 'A dream is not meant to be dreamed forever; instead, it''s meant for you to work hard and smart enough until success wakes you up from it.', 166, 0), (195206, 'Pay your bills, yes. But don''t invest in them. Invest in your dreams. What you invest in grows.', 25144, 0), (195207, 'Some people would tell you that it''s impossible for you to become successful in your line of passion. But don''t be distracted by them because it is only you that need to believe in your dream in order for it to manifest. The vindication of your success doesn''t need the whole world or anybody to cosign your passion for you.', 166, 0), (195208, 'when you do great things, think as if you missed the mark by an inch; walk as if you are yet to face the greatest task; talk as if you are yet to have the best preparation for the momentous moment and dream as if you are fighting a battalion of tasks', 4606, 0), (195209, 'I look forward to seeing you in the “jungle” as our warriors meet and join the battle drum that calls for unity in the struggle for breaking the chains of modern slavery—like the butterflies flying the skies and the birds over the seas, all are welcomed for both ear and eye—promises of victory are high, for even if unattainable today, tomorrow still holds the torch and dream, like fire of paradise, glory of life, glory of eternity!', 8254, 0), (195210, 'You are free to dream as big as you want, but always remember that every big dream comes with some big responsibilities. So be willing and courageous enough to step out of your comfort zone.', 166, 0), (195211, 'The person in love finds only a dream, a notion, an ideal. You fall in love with nothing but your own dreams—the only carriers of your true longings. Sometimes you manage to personify your dreams in another. Sometimes it’s not a single-player game. This doesn’t make love any less primal or selfish.', 26268, 0), (195212, 'Stop making some excuses on why you can''t pursue your true passion in life. You could start building your passion on the side until it grows big enough to substitute your regular job, and then you could concentrate fulltime on your passion and drive it to greatness.', 166, 0), (195213, 'The Classical Study (3)The Master has forgotten his hat.Without his hat he cannot fly.Without his hat his dreams escapeup.Without his hat he cannot tiphis hat to that woman passing bywhom he remembersfrom somewhere, as in a dream,a room in a dream or maybe a beach,a beach by the sea,blindingly white,hatless, he and she.', 35773, 0), (195214, 'Success has proven to us over and over again that one''s dream would become impossible to achieve, if one continuously convinces oneself to believe so.', 166, 0), (195215, 'My wish is to create a huge library of books.', 2878, 0), (195216, 'No dream is too big for God to shine the light of manifestation on.', 166, 0), (195217, 'Let''s not deceive ourselves by always praying to God to help us succeed in life, but then turn around and starve our dreams from actions; yet expecting God to perform some miracles in our lives.', 166, 0), (195218, 'Well at ease are the Sleepers for whom Existence is a shallow Dream.', 3061, 0), (195219, 'Soothing the exhaustionIn my soul,So I can fall back skyward,Safe in your arms,And survive to dream again.', 23446, 0), (195220, 'I was disoriented by the idea that men should ever leave the forest.', 10394, 0), (195221, 'Let us have no guiltLeft to wasteFor dreaming still.', 23446, 0), (195222, 'last night i dreamt AGAIN of a chaotic world, a lawless world..a world that was wounded with bullet holes, shattered glass & screams behind explosives harsh soundmy dreams, for some time now..so filled with shattered glass.just shattered glass. in a shattered world.', 23448, 0), (195223, 'Procrastination is definitely not your friend of your God''s given destiny. It is nothing but a dream stealer.', 166, 0), (195224, 'A dream is always risky, for there is a price to pay.', 34, 0), (195225, 'Don''t let the difficulties that come with your dream blur your vision of the prize ahead.', 166, 0), (195226, 'Success is what happens when you have given your dreams all that you think that you have in you, but still persist in giving them some more.', 166, 0), (195227, 'If we keep our dreams in our head they can be forgotten,If we write down our dreams they become tangible,Once they are physical, they have taken the first step in becoming attainable.', 8542, 0), (195228, 'Life supports what supports more of life', 1141, 0), (195229, 'No matter how difficult things get, never stop holding strong to your dreams; your time to shine is definitely coming.', 166, 0), (195230, 'First organizing it on paper isn''t just academic, it''s an applied prerequisite for manifestation.', 2747, 0), (195231, 'We are limited, not by our abilities, but by our vision. You gotta have a BIG vision to know what your abilities are. Don''t be afraid. Fear limits YOU and YOUR VISION. It''s okay to DREAM and dream BIG.', 14671, 0), (195232, 'Though your dream may be birth by you, it has eternal potential to impact lives and generations even after you.', 19626, 0), (195233, 'In walking or working your dream, arriving is a bad thing, because arriving makes you do things you said you wouldn’t do when you started.', 19626, 0), (195234, 'Remember when your dream was just an idea; never forget when nobody could see what you saw, when there was no win in sight.', 19626, 0), (195235, 'Life and situations will never improve to the point when living a dream becomes most conducive...honestly', 35774, 0), (195236, 'Provide me with an ink, paper, inspiration and place me on the high point on the edge with the sunset and sunrise, and I will make a masterpiece for you.', 20633, 0), (195237, 'He''s unconventionally attractive and yet coincidentally everything I''ve ever wanted.', 953, 0), (195238, 'She kept hoping that something would happen to rescue her from her own small-scale, predictable dreams.', 30, 0), (195239, 'Love is wanting to be with someone all the time.It is accepting the other person with all good qualities and bad and not wanting to change any of them. It is wanting to give affection and approval and comfort and everything that is oneself,demanding nothing in return. It is - love is very difficult, Julia. It is an ideal, rarely achieved in reality because we are all selfish and imperfect beings. It is a dream, a goal, something to be aimed for.', 5958, 0), (195240, 'CodaPerhaps to love is to learnto walk through this world.To learn to be silentlike the oak and the linden of the fable.To learn to see.Your glance scattered seeds.It planted a tree. I talkbecause you shake its leaves.', 8633, 0), (195241, 'Mandy loved the smell of a sunny day after a night of rain. The sun hit the orange puddles, the overgrown, soft, green grass on her lawn, and it beamed down through the orange steel mill smog, sending otherworldly, bizarre shadows across the concrete sidewalk.', 4547, 0), (195242, 'The flower drifted, light and open, gliding a path through still water like the faint stirrings of a dream.', 23946, 0), (195243, 'One dream, will suffice a thousand nightmares.', 3341, 0), (195244, 'Being near you for a day was at the top of my bucket list of the greatest life achievements, so this has by far exceeded my expectations and everyday has been magic.', 953, 0), (195245, 'If your dream is all about winning an ‪#oscar‬, a ‪‎grammy‬, an ‪#emmy‬, or another award, give up and quit now!Why dream for accolades, awards, recognition or celebrity status?Dream to learn, achieve, grow, sustain and succeed.You will be a happier person in life over trying to define your success or your dream by what others think of you.', 8380, 0), (195246, 'An extraordinary dream by lord charles wellesley. (Charlotte Bronte)''In this slumber i thought i was walking on the banks of a river... Which murmered over small pebbles at the bottom, gleaming like crystals through the silver stream'' ''and the green buds of the wild rose trees around were unopened'' ''and a mild warmth were shed from the sun... Then at its height in the blue sky', 42, 0), (195247, '                And into the close and mirrored catacombs of sleepWe''ll fall, and there in the faded light discover the bones,The dust, the bitter remains of someone who might have been                    Had we not taken his place.', 5859, 0), (195248, 'Tell me this is a nightmare', 1421, 0), (195249, 'The opportunity cost of an unlived dream is not only that dream, but also the dreams the dream was meant to inspire.', 10209, 0), (195250, 'The world is your oyster...YOU determine the value of the pearl!', 25834, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (195251, 'If you love something, you find a way to have it in your life. Opposers may take away your means and tools, but you simply turn to crude replacements, fashioning them from scraps if necessary. Threats only make you steal moments of secrecy to satisfy your love. And if it means but a morsel here and there, you accept each crumb gladly because nothing else can even begin to satisfy your hunger.', 1456, 0), (195252, 'Note for a moment do I take you for a truth that is real,'' Ivan exclaimed in what even amounted to fury. ''You are a falsehood, you are my illness, you are a ghost. Only I do not know how to destroy you, and perceive that for a certain time I must suffer you. You are a hallucination I am having. You are the embodiment of myself, but only of one side of me ... of my thoughts and emotions, though only those that are most loathsome and stupid. In that regard you might even be of interest to me, if only I had time to throw away on you ...', 57, 0), (195253, 'A place, where i can do anything.... is called dream.', 35775, 0), (195254, 'I didn’t want to dream of you anymore, so I quit sleeping.', 24815, 0), (195255, 'We wouldn''t want to live in a world where no one believed in themselves enough to make their own dreams come true.', 1738, 0), (195256, 'Entrepreneurs see what others can''t, do what others won''t, and accomplish what others dream.', 10209, 0), (195257, 'To be a success, water your dream with optimism and love.', 2586, 0), (195258, 'when a lifestyle is created from the existence of your dream, you dont leave any room for failure.', 3305, 0), (195259, 'Embrace your responsibility to dream big.', 11253, 0), (195260, 'I''m just a girl, with a pen and a dream', 3305, 0), (195261, 'As I look out at you all gathered here I want to say that I don''t see a room full of Parisians in top hats and diamonds and silk dresses. I don''t see bankers and housewives and store clerks. No. I address you all tonight as you truly are: wizards, mermaids, travelers, adventures, and magicians. You are the true dreamers.', 10099, 0), (195262, 'The dream that wakened me pushed at the veil of consciousness but could not burst through, and I was left wondering what I had known just a moment before.', 4408, 0), (195263, 'If you want to do something great, remember someone out there trying already to get that, I want you to be that some one.', 12584, 0), (195264, 'As I walked with my arms crossed to keep warm, I felt myself going numb. How long was I gone, I wondered. A few hours? Minutes? Days? There was no way to know. Maybe I was locked in that darkness all along and just woke from my dream... A marvelous dream.', 26402, 0), (195265, 'To dream only of what is ‘possible’ is to be fooled into believing that one is dreaming in the first place.', 4397, 0), (195266, 'We come to a house and walk down the small walkway to its backyard. In the yard there are two screens and a slide projector. People are seated in lawn chairs, watching slides of trees.', 127, 0), (195267, 'Every dream has a message. Pay attention!', 32656, 0), (195268, 'Write about the dream you see during consciousness.', 2586, 0), (195269, 'Dream, dare and discover.Care, share and inspire.', 2586, 0), (195270, 'Write about the dream you see during wakefulness.', 2586, 0), (195271, 'Go for the desire you dare to dream.', 2586, 0), (195272, 'A simple dream, a simple thoughtCan generate actions to shake the world.', 2586, 0), (195273, 'Write about the desire you dare to dream.', 2586, 0), (195274, 'Happiness is there when your dreams, hopes, and desires are compatible with your actions.', 2586, 0), (195275, '...dream BIG like a child!', 5043, 0), (195276, 'Some men see things as they are and ask why. Others dream things that never were and ask why not.', 266, 0), (195277, 'The beauty of life is in our dream . When our actions transform our dream to a reality we become a success.', 2586, 0), (195278, 'Fly beyond infinities.', 27136, 0), (195279, 'All her life, dreams had been her friends. Her dreams were unusually detailed, well-structured, colorful.', 133, 0), (195280, 'The death of a dreamer does not always bring about the death of his dreams.', 1660, 0), (195281, 'Athos was delighted to find he was going to fight an Englishman. We might say that was his dream.', 319, 0), (195282, 'When you dream for perfect life ahead, you may not get a fresh start always.Mend a little,bend a little. Find what you have, where you are. Adapt , improvise, move on.', 25838, 0), (195283, 'Your dream doesn''t have an expiration date.Take a deep breath and try again....', 35776, 0), (195284, 'The future hovered in front of her, and she rode Cruise towards it, her hands steady on the reins and her head among the clouds.', 25836, 0), (195285, 'I clung to the dream like a lifeline, the only thing worth keeping going for. That was why I had agreed to come here. I''d always said I would sell my soul for a pony of my own.', 25836, 0), (195286, 'Live in a place where people are revered for being clever, funny, and creative, instead of rich annoying, and on television. Where they inspire. Where they aspire. Where they dream of the perfect sentence, or the perfect drawing, or the perfect chord. Where singing a line that sums up your generation with a run of simple, cutting words is more valuable than a million Likes or Follows or dumbass Retweets.', 35777, 0), (195287, 'Dream!', 27136, 0), (195288, 'A dream may encourage us, but at the end of the day, it''s just a dream. We should also learn how to make a move.', 27136, 0), (195289, 'Life is a series of conflicts between the right way and the easy way each day.The thing is you head up straight. And when you make that choice. And when you decide turn your back to what''s comfortable, and safe and what someone calls common sense. So, that''s day one. From there, it''s only get tougher. But make sure it is something you really want because the easy-way always be there to wash you away. Each step in life comes to a decision and take another. Now You are on your way but You fight against an opponent you can''t see, but all you can feel among your heels. Feel him breathing down on your neck. That''s you. Your fears, your doubts, your insecurity all end up as an enemy within. Remember life is royal battle between You and You.', 13708, 0), (195290, 'Having the big picture in mind enables us to overcome the day to day routines that attempt to distract us from pursuing our dream.', 11326, 0), (195291, 'If only I had', 35778, 0), (195292, 'Its weird how i dream things that are worth writing.Its like God is writing them into my mind while i am sleeping and the moment i woke up i know i have to write what i dreamt', 35779, 0), (195293, 'Who will you be, my Little Ones? Will you dance for the fires of your youth and run at midnight to water’s edge, diving into summer’s heat? Will you ride a wild mare to any thought or dream or love of your making? Will you seek the artistry of your own infatuations and explore . . .', 23450, 0), (195294, 'This IS exactly how things look just before your dreams ignite!', 35780, 0), (195295, 'Sometimes all it takes is one Deep Breath and everything falls into place.', 35780, 0), (195296, 'I can do what I dream of doing, one breath and one step at a time.', 35780, 0), (195297, 'If you got a dream, you are good to go. The only extra luggage you will need is self-belief and perseverance.', 9273, 0), (195298, 'If you dreamed to have a tranquil life then do not bother either exasperate or infuriate other''s life. Dreaming a tranquil life is good but you cannot surmount it if you have a lot of foes indeed.', 35781, 0), (195299, 'Rest is luxury when you chasing your dreams, don''t get used to it and don''t prolong it when you get a chance at it.', 9273, 0), (195300, 'Life is serious conflicts between the right way and the easy way each day.The thing is you head up straight. And when you make that choice